Yes, I'm too lazy to type a brand-new README file.

Download the node.js tarball from the Debian project's archive here:

http://ftp.de.debian.org/debian/pool/main/n/nodejs/nodejs_0.10.7~dfsg1.orig.tar.gz

Uncompress it into this directory with the command

tar --strip-components=1 -xvzf ~/nodejs_0.10.7~dfsg1.orig.tar.gz

Then run the command `dpkg-buildpackage`.  It'll take a long time in a real
RasPi, so you might want to consider running it inside of a QEMU VM.

--The Doctor
